Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago says inflation will be well contained and will remain in the mid-point despite the general rise in risk. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Reserve Bank has cut interest rates by 100 basis points. The repo rate is now 5.25% from 6.25%. This is an attempt to help ease the burden on consumers. Governor, Lesetja Kganyago says Covid-19 will retard global and domestic growth Â for at least the first half of this year.